The paper deals with the problem of constructing a differentially private synopsis for classification analyses, which involves privacy-preserving data release and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), which deals with privacy and security issues in computer science. The paper also involves data management and machine learning, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DB (Databases) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) categories. The paper proposes a new approach for selecting an optimal partition of the dataset, which involves data-aware and privacy-budget-aware threshold, suggesting that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) category. Finally, the paper involves the use of a novel quality function to evaluate an attribute's relevance to the classification label variable, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category.
